A template for analyzing runs

Fergus Fettes

import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
# import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
# import seaborn as sns
import plotly.express as px
import gpxpy

from bs4 import BeautifulSoup
import requests
import re

from duckduckgo_search import ddg_images
from fastcore.all import *

# Get my traces
URL_BASE = "https://www.openstreetmap.org/"
username = "Fergus Fettes"
URL = f"https://www.openstreetmap.org/user/{username}/traces"

# Get the gpx files from the page
def get_gpx_files(url):
    "Get the gpx files from the page"

    # Get the page
    page = requests.get(url)

    # Parse the page
    soup = BeautifulSoup(page.content, "html.parser")

    # Get the links with 'gpx' in the description
    links = soup.find_all("a", string=re.compile("gpx"))

    # Get the trace number
    trace_numbers = [int(link["href"].split("/")[-1]) for link in links]
    return [f"{URL_BASE}/trace/{trace_number}/data" for trace_number in trace_numbers]

# Get the gpx files
gpx_files = get_gpx_files(URL)

# Make temp dir
# tmp_dir = Path("/tmp/gpx")
# tmp_dir.mkdir(exist_ok=True)
# [urlsave(gpx_file, tmp_dir/f"{i}.gpx") for i, gpx_file in enumerate(gpx_files)]

filenames = [f"/tmp/gpx/{i}.gpx" for i in range(len(gpx_files))]

# Load the gpx files
gpx_files = [gpxpy.parse(open(filename, "r")) for filename in filenames]

# Get the data from the gpx files
def get_data(gpx_file):
    "Get the data from the gpx file"
    data = []
    for track in gpx_file.tracks:
        for segment in track.segments:
            for point in segment.points:
                data.append(
                    {
                        "lat": point.latitude,
                        "lon": point.longitude,
                        "elev": point.elevation,
                        "time": point.time,
                    }
                )
    return pd.DataFrame(data)

# Get the data
data = [get_data(gpx_file) for gpx_file in gpx_files]
df = pd.concat(data)

# Locaize the time
df["time"] = df["time"].dt.tz_convert("Europe/Prague")
df["time"] = df["time"].dt.tz_localize(None)

# Order by time
df = df.sort_values("time")

df.head()
# df.info()
# df.describe()

# fig_1 = px.scatter(df, x='lon', y='lat', template='plotly_dark')
# fig_1.show()

# fig_2 = px.line(df, x='time', y='elev', template='plotly_dark')
# fig_2.show()

# fig_3 = px.scatter_3d(df, x='lon', y='lat', z='elev', color='elev', template='plotly_dark')
# fig_3.update_traces(marker=dict(size=2), selector=dict(mode='markers'))
# fig_3.show()

fig_4 = px.line_mapbox(
  df,
  lat='lat',
  lon='lon',
  hover_name='time',
  mapbox_style="open-street-map",
  zoom=13
)
fig_4.update_layout(margin={"r":0,"t":0,"l":0,"b":0})
fig_4.show()
Code 
from geopy import distance
from math import sqrt, floor
import datetime

# first create lists to store the results, these will be appended ot the dataframe at the end
# Note: i'll be working from the gps_points object directly and then appending results into the dataframe. It would make a lot more sense to operate directly on the dataframe.

delta_elev = [0]    # change in elevation between records
delta_time = [0]    # time interval between records

delta_sph2d = [0]   # segment distance from spherical geometry only
delta_sph3d = [0]   # segment distance from spherical geometry, adjusted for elevation
dist_sph2d = [0]   # cumulative distance from spherical geometry only
dist_sph3d = [0]   # cumulative distance from spherical geometry, adjusted for elevation

delta_geo2d = [0]   # segment distance from geodesic method only
delta_geo3d = [0]   # segment distance from geodesic method, adjusted for elevation
dist_geo2d = [0]   # cumulative distance from geodesic method only
dist_geo3d = [0]   # cumulative distance from geodesic method, adjusted for elevation


for idx in range(1, len(df)):
    start = df.iloc[idx-1]
    end = df.iloc[idx]

    # elevation
    temp_delta_elev = end.elev - start.elev
    delta_elev.append(temp_delta_elev)

    # time
    temp_delta_time = (end.time - start.time).total_seconds()
    delta_time.append(temp_delta_time)

    # distance from spherical model
    temp_delta_sph2d = distance.great_circle((start.lat, start.lon), (end.lat, end.lon)).m
    delta_sph2d.append(temp_delta_sph2d)
    dist_sph2d.append(dist_sph2d[-1] + temp_delta_sph2d)

    temp_delta_sph3d = sqrt(temp_delta_sph2d**2 + temp_delta_elev**2)
    delta_sph3d.append(temp_delta_sph3d)
    dist_sph3d.append(dist_sph3d[-1] + temp_delta_sph3d)

# Simple time
simple_time = df.time.max() - df.time.min()

# Simple elevation
simple_elev = df.elev.max() - df.elev.min()

# dump the lists into the dataframe
df['delta_elev'] = delta_elev
df['delta_time'] = delta_time
df['delta_sph2d'] = delta_sph2d
df['delta_sph3d'] = delta_sph3d
df['dist_sph2d'] = dist_sph2d
df['dist_sph3d'] = dist_sph3d
df['simple_time'] = simple_time
df['simple_elev'] = simple_elev
df['inst_mps'] = df['delta_sph3d'] / df['delta_time']
df['inst_kph'] = df['inst_mps'] * 3.6

# Fill the NaN values in inst_mps and inst_kph
df['inst_mps'] = df['inst_mps'].fillna(0)
df['inst_kph'] = df['inst_kph'].fillna(0)
Code 
# check bulk results
print(
  f"Spherical Distance 2D: {dist_sph2d[-1]/1000}km \n"
  f"Spherical Distance 3D: {dist_sph3d[-1]/1000}km \n"
  f"Elevation Correction: {(dist_sph3d[-1]) - (dist_sph2d[-1])} meters \n"
  f"Total Time: {str(datetime.timedelta(seconds=sum(delta_time)))}\n"
  f"Simple Time: {simple_time}\n"
  f"Simple Elevation: {simple_elev}"
  )

fig_5 = px.line(df, x='time', y='dist_sph3d', template='plotly_dark')
fig_5.show()

fig_6 = px.line(df, x='dist_sph3d', y='delta_elev', template='plotly_dark')
fig_6.show()

fig_8 = px.histogram(df, x='inst_kph', template='plotly_dark')
fig_8.update_traces(xbins=dict(start=0, end=20, size=0.1))
fig_8.show()

df_moving = df[df['inst_mps'] >= 0.9]
avg_kph = (sum((df['inst_kph'] * df['delta_time'])) / sum(df['delta_time']))
avg_mov_kph = (sum((df_moving['inst_kph'] * df_moving['delta_time'])) / sum(df_moving['delta_time']))

print(f"Maximum Speed: {round((df['inst_kph'].max(axis=0)), 2)} kph")
print(f"Average Speed: {round((avg_kph), 2)} kph")
print(f"Average Moving Speed: {round((avg_mov_kph), 2)} kph")
print(f"Moving Time: {str(datetime.timedelta(seconds=sum(df_moving['delta_time'])))}")
elev_gain = sum(list(filter(lambda x : x > 0, df['delta_elev'])))
print(f"Total Elevation Gain: {round(elev_gain, 2)}")
Spherical Distance 2D: 19.20946446307514km 
Spherical Distance 3D: 19.660483582642765km 
Elevation Correction: 451.01911956762706 meters

df['avg_mps_roll'] = df['inst_mps'].rolling(20, center=True).mean()
fig_16 = px.line(df, x='time', y=['inst_mps', 'avg_mps_roll'], template='plotly_dark')
fig_16.show()

```{python}
# check bulk results
print(
  f"Spherical Distance 2D: {dist_sph2d[-1]/1000}km \n"
  f"Spherical Distance 3D: {dist_sph3d[-1]/1000}km \n"
  f"Elevation Correction: {(dist_sph3d[-1]) - (dist_sph2d[-1])} meters \n"
  f"Total Time: {str(datetime.timedelta(seconds=sum(delta_time)))}\n"
  f"Simple Time: {simple_time}\n"
  f"Simple Elevation: {simple_elev}"
  )

fig_5 = px.line(df, x='time', y='dist_sph3d', template='plotly_dark')
fig_5.show()

fig_6 = px.line(df, x='dist_sph3d', y='delta_elev', template='plotly_dark')
fig_6.show()

fig_8 = px.histogram(df, x='inst_kph', template='plotly_dark')
fig_8.update_traces(xbins=dict(start=0, end=20, size=0.1))
fig_8.show()

df_moving = df[df['inst_mps'] >= 0.9]
avg_kph = (sum((df['inst_kph'] * df['delta_time'])) / sum(df['delta_time']))
avg_mov_kph = (sum((df_moving['inst_kph'] * df_moving['delta_time'])) / sum(df_moving['delta_time']))

print(f"Maximum Speed: {round((df['inst_kph'].max(axis=0)), 2)} kph")
print(f"Average Speed: {round((avg_kph), 2)} kph")
print(f"Average Moving Speed: {round((avg_mov_kph), 2)} kph")
print(f"Moving Time: {str(datetime.timedelta(seconds=sum(df_moving['delta_time'])))}")
elev_gain = sum(list(filter(lambda x : x > 0, df['delta_elev'])))
print(f"Total Elevation Gain: {round(elev_gain, 2)}")
```
